snippet.textDisplay:
@Evilriku13"Due to a combination of the second disc content being almost entirely composed of single boss battles surrounded by character narration and a large number of unused assets and fragments that can be found included in the code on the second disc, there has long been speculation the game was rushed at the end of production. If this happened or why has never been confirmed by anyone involved in the game's development. While the game is considered 'finished', signs of rushed development are found throughout both discs, and several story threads were left incomplete."   "There is mention in Perfect Works that there were scheduling issues near the end"
Also, it is rumoured that the resources were shifted for FF8 development, not FF7. 
Disc 2 people sit in chairs talking which is why it was 'bad.'

